<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Minimalist_music&amp;action=edit&amp;section=14" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://artofthestates.org/cgi-bin/genresearch.pl?genre=minimalist" class="external text" title="http://artofthestates.org/cgi-bin/genresearch.pl?genre=minimalist" rel="nofollow">Art of the States: minimalist</a> minimalist works by American composers, including audio samples.</li>
<li><a href="http://arted.osu.edu/160/11_MinimalMusic.php" class="external text" title="http://arted.osu.edu/160/11_MinimalMusic.php" rel="nofollow">Art and Music Since 1945: Introduction to Minimal Music</a>, from <a href="/wiki/Ohio_State_University" title="Ohio State University">Ohio State University</a>'s Department of <a href="/wiki/Art_Education" title="Art Education" class="mw-redirect">Art Education</a>.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.newmusicbox.org/page.nmbx?id=31tp00" class="external text" title="http://www.newmusicbox.org/page.nmbx?id=31tp00" rel="nofollow">Minimal Music, Maximal Impact</a>, by <a href="/wiki/Kyle_Gann" title="Kyle Gann">Kyle Gann</a>, with a more comprehensive list of early minimalists.</li>
</ul>


